<h3>
    The label tag
</h3>
<p>
    The label tag is used to label certain input tags. It has a <code>for</code>
    attribute which identifies what input to attach it to. As such, 
    the <code>for</code> attribute of the label tag must match its 
    input's tag <code>id</code> attribute. 
</p>
<pre><code class="lang-html">
&lt;!-- 
for = lname and id = lname 
--&gt;
&lt;label for='lname'>Last name:&lt;/label&gt;
&lt;input type='text' id='lname' name='lname'&gt;
</code></pre>

<h3>
    The Name Attribute
</h3>
<p>
    Each input field must have a <code>name</code> attribute, or the form 
    will not work.
</p>

